Smart things inspire!Decto is an early stage manufacturing company, that produces personal smart sensors and detectors. We are passionate about smart things that make our everyday-life smarter, easier and healthier. Therefore, together with the powerful and educating Decto software our products give you the tools and the knowledge to improve the quality of your life.The Decto team is developing and producing products for everyone at an affordable price. Using components from EU and producing the products in EU we can guarantee the best quality. Our module concept is driven by the concern about the environment. Decto smart sensors are equipped with microprocessor and are more environmentally friendly as they have no batteries, displays, speakers, cables and extra buttons. Those things are already in your smartphone. Use them!Products:
AIR - measures air temperature, humidity, and pressure;
LUMEN - measures the intensity of light and luminance;
ALCO - measures ethanol level in breath;
BT MATE - a portable device, which makes it possible to leave the sensor to a desired location to take measurements. The device comes in handy when you want to keep your smart phone with you, rather than leave it to a certain location for measuring, or you would like to use different sensors simultaneously. BT MATE connects to your smartphone via Bluetooth. BT MATE is essential for Apple users.
The next product in the Decto series is called NUC, which is a personal radioactive wave detector to protect you and the people around you from the danger that cannot be seen with a bare eye. It helps to discover beta and gamma waves, sum up exposure dosage, pin the radioactive places on the map, warn others about the danger and report the authorities to clean up the waste.Decto needs your support to bring this valuable product to the global market. There is a lot of radioactive waste around us and it poses a threat to everyone! Show your support and get your own personal Decto NUC with a pre-sell price!First 100 pcs - $69 and gift BT MATE + delivery101- 500 pcs - $69 + delivery501- ... pcs - $79 + deliveryFriends Pack: 3 NUC's and 3 BT MATE's - $290Re-seller Pack 20 pcs : $1290 + deliveryBe part of the personal detector story!FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONSWhere did you get the idea to create Decto NUC?The Internal Security Services (ISS) found an 85-kilo container in Estonia, designed to hold radioactive material! Decto NUC was created to locate such dangerous materials. It is important to prevent the exposure of dangerous radioactive materials and to protect us from radioactive sickness! Article about the findings: http://news.err.ee/v/politics/environment/4a1b5112-b31d-48e2-94ca-07b5fd4d2764/iss-finds-radioactive-substance-container-near-tallinnPRODUCT FEATURESHow do Decto products work?1.  Firstly, download the Decto Free or Decto Premium software to your smart device.2.  Open the app.3.  Connect your personal DECTO device directly, using a micro USB (OTG supported), or via Bluetooth with Decto BT MATE.4.  The product is ready to take measurements. If necessary, please, read the manual, which is under the sign “?”.Why should I use Decto products?Decto products are designed to help to improve the quality of your life. The products are your personal smart detectors and sensors.There are sensors and detectors already available. Why should I use yours?Decto sensors and detectors are smart and small, light weighted, environmentally friendly, available at an affordable price and supported with an educating software.Do you like to travel around? Getting a new home in another area? Decto products are for you then! Measure the air temperature, air pressure, humidity, the intensity of light/luminance and radiation with the Decto devices wherever you go.How portable are the sensors? How much do they weigh?Decto sensors weigh about 0.5-1.4 ounces (10-15 grams), you can easily keep it in your pocket or handbag.Do I need to download the app to use a Decto sensor/detector?Yes, hardware needs software in order to work, even a printer. You can download a Free or Premium Decto app from Google Play or App Store. Drivers for Windows, Mac and Linux will soon be available.Will Decto sensors work with any smart device?Sensors/detectors are compatible with iOS 9.0+ devices and Android 4.3+ devices with Bluetooth and OTG (on-the-go) support. Is the Decto mobile app available free of charge?There is a Decto Free and Decto Premium version. Decto Free version provides you with the measurement results, time and date, easy sharing and location (coordinates), notification function, the usage of one sensor at a time. Decto Premium provides you some handy extras: map view, usage of multiple sensors simultaneously and camera function. If there is a necessity for those features, then consider downloading a Premium version (one-time fee) and use it in all account linked smart devices.Will I receive any alerts?Yes, you can set minimum and maximum values in your app and get immediate notification, when the measured results are out of the previously defined level. All the notifications can be customized in the settings section.There’s a blue LED light in all Decto products. Why?Blue LED light is an indicator, which shows that the sensor/detector is connected to your smart device and that your smart device supports OTG (on-to-go). If the LED does not light up (or if you are using an iPhone, a tablet or a PC), then we recommend to use Decto BT MATE to connect via bluetooth.  TECHNICAL QUESTIONSHow trustworthy are the measured values?All sensors/detectors are pre-calibrated by the sensor/detector manufacturer and go through calibration procedure on our production line to increase its accuracy. Our partner in the field of calibration is Metrosert Ltd. They perform the calibration and verification of measuring instruments, certification of products and management systems in Estonia.How long will the battery last?Smart sensors and detectors do not have a battery. They work while being attached to you smart phone and use its battery. BT MATE has a 380mhA Li-ion battery and it lasts differently for each sensor. For example, Decto NUC consumes a lot of energy, so it takes 36 hours from being fully charged to empty.  Are the sensors/detectors waterproof?No, they are not. What is the operating temperature?Recommended operating temperature for Decto sensors/detectors is from -40°C to +85°C. There is a limitation due to the processor recommended conditions.Can the measured sensor/detector data be saved and shared?Yes, your data, as well as location via GPS, can be saved to our secure cloud and/or shared publicly. Decto application also works as a "big data" map and everyone can make a contribution by sharing air pollution, radiation, temperature etc related measurements on a map. Sharing, of course, is not compulsory and can be edited from the settings.DISTRIBUTIONWhat happens to the money you raise?Your money will be used to invest in mass-production: tooling, manufacturing setup and component parts.When will the NUC and mates ship?According to the plan, in May 2016.Where will you ship?We ship worldwide!Do they come with a warranty?Yes! We offer a 12 month manufacturers’ warranty with all our products.I am a distributor. How do I contact you?Please contact info@decto.eu.  CUSTOMER SUPPORTDo you have customer service and technical support?We sure do! You can contact us via email - info@decto.eu. We would be glad to give an answer to all your questions. For extra information, please visit our website – decto.eu.Can I change or cancel my perk?Indiegogo has now made it easier than ever to upgrade your perks. You can do so on the contributions tab of your Indiegogo profile. See more information on how to do this here: https://support.indiegogo.com/hc/en-us/articles/526756-How-to-Upgrade-Your-PerkTo get a refund on your perk contribution, while the campaign is active, please email support@indiegogo.com. After the campaign, we will evaluate refunds on a case-by-case basis but are not obligated to do so.I have a problem backing you up?Please contact support@indiegogo.com.Will there be continued support/updates for the app?Sure! We already have a roadmap for new features. If you have any suggestions please contact us - info@decto.eu.
